    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2fd91596_97dca4a1",
        "filename": "src/core/SkCanvas.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 2213,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T15:53:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is there a convention that lets us always funnel through quick_reject() instead of breaking it down into its constituent pieces for these special cases?  E.g.\n\n    if (quick_reject(this, this-\u003egetLocalClipBounds(), paint)) {\n        return;\n    }\n\nI\u0027m wondering if we can get it funneled down so that only quick_reject() needs to know the rules (e.g. that all bounds that are isFinite() is rejected, which is pretty counterintuitive for ±inf).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2211,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 2213,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "70b0c520af88e5b162a5f23d73f19e7b4db8f513",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ff472f43_1ede0194",
        "filename": "src/core/SkCanvas.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 2213,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T19:10:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve never really thought about it until now, but what does drawPaint() mean to do if a paint has a mask filter or a path effect on it?\n\nI don\u0027t think they make much sense, so really the paint canonized version should be filled w/ no path effect or mask filter. If that\u0027s the case, then simply getLocalClipBounds() would work. The downside to that is it involves some matrix transforms from device space to local space. drawPaint is weird in that there isn\u0027t local geometry associated with it. For that reason, I\u0027m okay having it just check if the paint draws nothing and if the clip is empty, so long as all the others can go through the funnel.",
      "parentUuid": "2fd91596_97dca4a1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2211,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 2213,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "70b0c520af88e5b162a5f23d73f19e7b4db8f513",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9ba6d5f9_ea980684",
        "filename": "src/core/SkCanvas.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 2213,
      "author": {
        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T19:33:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e drawPaint is weird in that there isn\u0027t local geometry associated with it\n\nIsn\u0027t the geometry \"everywhere\", clipped down by the clip as usual, so... the clip?  Then getLocalClipBounds() does exactly return the bounds of the geometry.\n\nBut yeah, if we have to have one weirdo case that\u0027s unlike the others, this is a good one to be that weirdo.",
      "parentUuid": "ff472f43_1ede0194",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2211,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 2213,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "70b0c520af88e5b162a5f23d73f19e7b4db8f513",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
