      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T19:43:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this might be another spot where we can be a lot clearer if we favor simplicity, e.g.\n\n   SkPaint paint \u003d userPaint;\n   paint.setStyle(SkPaint::kFill_Style);\n   paint.setMaskFilter(nullptr);\n   \nor\n\n   SkPaint paint \u003d userPaint ? *userPaint : SkPaint{};\n   paint.setStyle(SkPaint::kStroke_Style);\n   paint.setPathEffect(nullptr);\n\netc, and not introduce any abstraction like init_paint() unless it does actually abstract over some sort of non-obvious constraint, like say, mask filter and path effect always being null\u0027d at the same time, never separately.",
      "parentUuid": "715e7d8e_563fe22e",
      "revId": "70b0c520af88e5b162a5f23d73f19e7b4db8f513",
