      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T21:46:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I played around a bit with this, and it definitely is more readable in simple cases. I will use it like that for drawVertices, drawPatch, and drawPoints, since they are the only other calls besides the drawImage family that needs cleaning up.\n\nHowever, the drawImage family has 6 virtuals that all need to be cleaned the same way, and they all can interact with the image filter optimizations similarly to how AutoLayerForImageFilter does. I plan on keeping some form of init_image_paint for them.\n\nThis CL: https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/341056 moves them to copy-on-write, mostly because AutoLayerForImageFilter uses copy-on-write and it helps simplify the optimization logic.\n\nOnce SkDrawIter goes away, the updated draw code will only use an auto-layer if there\u0027s an image filter. At that point, I feel comfortable having AutoLayer stop using copy-on-write entirely and then we can have init_image_paint and the image filter optimizations all operate on plain SkPaints directly. AutoLayer will just take an SkPaint* that it may modify, and draw calls will make a local copy of their paint, if they haven\u0027t already, before making the auto-layer.",
      "parentUuid": "df9e1cca_4d97d60e",
      "revId": "70b0c520af88e5b162a5f23d73f19e7b4db8f513",
